---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="The Complete Guide to Modern Music Production — Blog" description="Master the fundamentals of music production from recording to mastering">
  <!-- Article Header -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[50vh] w-full text-white pt-32 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <img 
      src="/assets/services/music.png" 
      alt="Music Production Guide" 
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-black/80 via-black/70 to-black/50"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-16 pt-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-[#D234C7]/20 text-[#D234C7] rounded-full">
          Production
        </span>
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">January 5, 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">The Complete Guide to Modern Music Production</h1>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-200">
        <span>By Marcus Chen</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>12 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article Content -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 md:px-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Music production is the art and science of creating, recording, mixing, and mastering songs. Whether you're an aspiring producer or an artist looking to understand the creative process, this comprehensive guide will walk you through every stage of modern music production.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Pre-Production: The Foundation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Before recording a single note, thorough pre-production is essential. This phase involves:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Song arrangement and structure planning</li>
        <li>Instrumentation decisions</li>
        <li>Demo recording and approval</li>
        <li>Studio booking and equipment selection</li>
        <li>Sound design conceptualization</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Recording: Capturing the Performance</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The recording phase captures the raw performances that will become your final track. Key considerations include acoustic environment, microphone selection, preamp settings, and monitoring setup. Professional recording requires technical expertise, quality equipment, and experienced engineering.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Editing and Timing Correction</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Once recordings are captured, editing ensures timing accuracy and performance consistency. This includes vocal editing, drum quantization, and timing adjustments. Subtle editing can elevate a good performance into a professional-quality track.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Mixing: Crafting the Blend</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Mixing is where individual recordings are combined into a cohesive stereo image. This involves balancing levels, panning, EQ, compression, effects, and spatial processing. Great mixing captures the listener's attention and guides them through the song's emotional journey.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Mastering: The Final Polish</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Mastering is the final step before distribution. It optimizes the mix for all playback systems while maintaining the artistic intent. Professional mastering ensures your music translates perfectly across earbuds, car speakers, and concert systems.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Essential Tools and Technology</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Modern producers typically use DAWs (Digital Audio Workstations) like Pro Tools, Logic Pro, or Ableton Live. Combined with quality monitors, interfaces, and microphones, these tools enable professional-quality production from any studio environment.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Music production is both an art and a technical discipline. By understanding each phase and investing in your skills and equipment, you can create music that resonates with listeners worldwide.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Author Info -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-[#D234C7] to-[#32BEF1]"></div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Marcus Chen</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Audio engineer and producer specializing in music production and mastering.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-12 pt-12 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/blog/when-to-start-singing" class="text-[#D234C7] font-semibold hover:underline">← Previous Article</a>
        <a href="/blog/mixing-mistakes" class="text-[#D234C7] font-semibold hover:underline">Next Article →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
